<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Mosaigo — Composable Pipeline Engine for Go</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Mosaigo is an open-source pipeline engine for Go. Compose typed, self-describing steps into pipelines for any domain: data processing, computer vision, IoT, audio, or anything that flows."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="topnav">
      <a href="/hub/" class="topnav-logo">
        <img src="/images/mozzy-icon.webp" alt="mosaigo" />
        mosaigo
      </a>
      <div class="topnav-links">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="topnav-link">Docs</a>
        <a href="/hub/mosoptics/" class="topnav-link">mosoptics</a>
        <a href="/hub/mosii/" class="topnav-link">mosii</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Turn small steps into a <span class="accent">big vision</span></h1>
      <p class="tagline">Mosaigo (mosaic-go) is a composable pipeline engine for Go that handles the hard parts so you can focus on what matters.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-install">
        <span class="prompt">$</span> go get github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo@latest
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge" style="margin-top: 16px;"><span class="dot"></span> Open source &middot; Pure Go</div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Why Mosaigo</div>
      <h2>Every step is a tile. Together, they're a picture.</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Single-purpose steps that each do one thing, composed into pipelines through configuration or at runtime. Strong typing across every boundary cuts boilerplate and catches mismatches before anything runs.</p>
      <div class="diff-grid">
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(42,127,191,0.12);color:var(--primary);">&#9881;</div>
          <h3>Type-Safe Generic Steps</h3>
          <p><code>TypedEngineStep[TIN, TOUT]</code> catches payload mismatches at compile time. Every step declares its input, output, config schema, and metadata through <code>StepDef</code>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(200,152,42,0.12);color:var(--accent);">&#9670;</div>
          <h3>Self-Describing Pipeline</h3>
          <p>Steps register themselves with full metadata. The framework auto-generates step catalogs, validates pipeline wiring before execution, and serializes issues to REST/WebSocket.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(58,143,92,0.12);color:var(--success);">&#9201;</div>
          <h3>Zero-Alloc Hot Path</h3>
          <p>Designed for real-time: pre-allocated buffers, zero-copy payload passing. Init() allocates, Process() is allocation-free, Close() releases. 120fps camera pipelines, not batch ETL.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(109,179,224,0.12);color:var(--light);">&#9783;</div>
          <h3>Built-In Observability</h3>
          <p>Every step automatically tracks latency via <code>MarkTime</code>. Topic pub/sub enables multi-engine architectures. Studio UI shows live pipeline graphs with per-step timing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(181,48,48,0.12);color:var(--error);">&#8644;</div>
          <h3>Hexagonal by Default</h3>
          <p>Steps never import infrastructure. Assembly happens at the top. Ports define contracts, adapters are swappable by config. Your step doesn't know about routers or drivers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(107,107,120,0.12);color:var(--text-secondary);">&#9874;</div>
          <h3>Config, YAML, or API</h3>
          <p>Three ways to build pipelines: programmatic Go API, YAML factory from the step registry, or web service payload via REST/WebSocket. Same validation, same steps.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">In practice</div>
      <h2>A pipeline in 15 lines</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Build, validate, and run. Every step comes from the registry, wired by the engine, observable by default.</p>
      <div class="code-showcase">
        <div>
          <div class="code-header">main.go</div>
          <div class="code-block" set:html={`<span class="kw">package</span> main

<span class="kw">import</span> (
    <span class="st">"github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo/engine"</span>
    <span class="st">"github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo/mos"</span>
)

<span class="kw">func</span> <span class="fn">main</span>() {
    <span class="cm">// Build from registered steps</span>
    eng := engine.<span class="fn">NewBuilder</span>(<span class="st">"my-pipeline"</span>).
        <span class="fn">AddByName</span>(<span class="st">"capture.session"</span>).
        <span class="fn">AddByName</span>(<span class="st">"vision.detect.ultraface"</span>).
        <span class="fn">AddByName</span>(<span class="st">"vision.gaze.l2cs"</span>).
        <span class="fn">Build</span>()

    <span class="cm">// Validate the full pipeline, all issues, not fail-fast</span>
    <span class="kw">if</span> issues := eng.<span class="fn">Validate</span>(); <span class="fn">len</span>(issues) &gt; <span class="st">0</span> {
        mos.<span class="fn">LogIssues</span>(issues)
        <span class="kw">return</span>
    }

    eng.<span class="fn">Run</span>() <span class="cm">// blocks, processes frames, observable via Studio</span>
}`} />
        </div>
        <div class="code-text" style="padding-top:32px;">
          <h3>What's happening here</h3>
          <p>Steps are resolved from the global <code>StepDef</code> registry by name. Each step was registered at init time with its config type, I/O payloads, and metadata.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Steps compile in, no dynamic plugins, no reflection at runtime</li>
            <li>The validator walks the full pipeline and collects every issue</li>
            <li>Process() is the hot path, zero allocation, MarkTime instrumented</li>
            <li>Topic pub/sub enables multi-engine architectures at different frame rates</li>
            <li>Config overridable: defaults &lt; YAML &lt; env var &lt; runtime API</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="text-align:center;">
      <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
      <h2>Metadata-driven composition</h2>
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">Every step describes itself completely. The framework uses that metadata to validate pipelines, generate catalogs, serve config schemas, and power the Studio UI, all automatically.</p>
      <div class="arch-visual">
        <div class="arch-layer" style="background:rgba(200,152,42,0.15);color:var(--accent);border:1px solid rgba(200,152,42,0.3);">
          Your Product <span class="desc">Compose steps, configure via YAML/API, ship</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-arrow">assembles &#8595;</div>
        <div class="arch-layer" style="background:rgba(42,127,191,0.15);color:var(--primary);border:1px solid rgba(42,127,191,0.3);">
          Domain Step Libraries <span class="desc">CV, IoT, ETL, audio, or your own, all TypedEngineStep</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-arrow">built on &#8595;</div>
        <div class="arch-layer" style="background:rgba(27,79,122,0.3);color:var(--light);border:1px solid rgba(27,79,122,0.5);">
          Mosaigo <span class="desc">Engine, pipeline, typed steps, topics, config, validation, Studio</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="arch-caption">Mosaigo is domain-agnostic. Your step libraries bring the domain knowledge. Mosaigo brings the composition, observability, and runtime.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">0</div><div class="label">CGo in the core</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">3</div><div class="label">Pipeline construction modes</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">0</div><div class="label">Allocations in Process()</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">100%</div><div class="label">Steps self-describing</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">Open</div><div class="label">Source</div></div>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Ecosystem</div>
      <h2>What you can build with Mosaigo</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">From data pipelines to real-time computer vision, Mosaigo provides the composable foundation.</p>
      <div class="portfolio-grid">
        <div class="portfolio-card">
          <img src="/images/portfolio-pipeline.webp" alt="Data pipeline visualization" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Composable Pipelines</h3>
            <p>Type-safe steps snap together like tiles. Build complex data flows from simple, reusable pieces.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-card">
          <img src="/images/mozzy-eyes2.webp" alt="Computer vision and gaze tracking" loading="lazy" style="border:none;" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Computer Vision</h3>
            <p>Face detection, gaze estimation, and stereo processing, all as pipeline steps via mosoptics.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-card">
          <img src="/images/portfolio-mosii.webp" alt="Eye gaze communication board" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Assistive Communication</h3>
            <p>mosii aims to turn eye gaze into communication for people with motor disabilities.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-card">
          <img src="/images/portfolio-hardware.webp" alt="Edge computing device with stereo camera" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Edge Hardware</h3>
            <p>Run on Jetson Orin, Raspberry Pi, or any edge device. GPU-accelerated inference at the edge.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-card">
          <img src="/images/portfolio-studio.webp" alt="Studio observability dashboard" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Studio Dashboard</h3>
            <p>Live pipeline visualization with per-step latency, throughput metrics, and camera preview.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="portfolio-card">
          <img src="/images/portfolio-steps.webp" alt="Step catalog mosaic" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Step Catalog</h3>
            <p>Browse, compose, and configure from a growing library of self-describing pipeline steps.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Get started</div>
      <h2>From zero to pipeline in minutes</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Pick your path: build from code or explore the architecture.</p>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <img src="/images/feature-getstarted.webp" alt="Quick start with Go code" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Quick Start Guide</h3>
            <p>Install Mosaigo, create your first pipeline, and see it run, all in a few minutes. The framework handles the wiring.</p>
            <a href="/getting-started/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <img src="/images/feature-architecture.webp" alt="Three-layer architecture" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>Architecture Guide</h3>
            <p>Understand the three-layer design: engine framework, domain step libraries, and your product on top. Clean boundaries, clear contracts.</p>
            <a href="/getting-started/" class="btn btn-secondary">Read More</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Iterate fast</div>
      <h2>Build alternatives, not commitments</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Mosaigo is built for experimentation. Don't pick an algorithm, try three. Steps are cheap to write, fast to swap, and the framework measures everything so you can compare empirically.</p>
      <div class="eco-grid">
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge" style="background:rgba(42,127,191,0.15);color:var(--primary);">compose</div>
          <h3>Snap steps together</h3>
          <p>Each step is a single-purpose tile with typed input and output. Rearrange, replace, or duplicate any tile without touching the rest. The pipeline is a composition, not a monolith.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge" style="background:rgba(200,152,42,0.15);color:var(--accent);">configure</div>
          <h3>Runtime-swappable config</h3>
          <p>Every step declares its config schema via struct tags. Override via YAML, environment variables, or runtime API, no recompile. Defaults &lt; file &lt; env &lt; API, always.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge" style="background:rgba(58,143,92,0.15);color:var(--success);">measure</div>
          <h3>See what's actually happening</h3>
          <p>MarkTime on every step. Per-step latency in the API. Topic throughput metrics. Studio dashboard. You can't improve what you can't see, and Mosaigo makes sure you see everything.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Values</div>
      <h2>What Mosaigo believes</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">These aren't rules to follow. They're the reason the framework exists.</p>
      <div class="principle-grid">
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">01</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Composition over configuration</h4>
            <p>Pipelines are assembled from independent steps, not configured from a mega-YAML. Each step does one thing. Swap, reorder, or duplicate any tile without touching the others.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">02</div>
          <div>
            <h4>The compiler is your first reviewer</h4>
            <p>Go generics catch payload mismatches at build time. If your step expects <code>[TIN]</code> and the previous step outputs something else, you know before you run.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">03</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Metadata is not optional</h4>
            <p>Every step declares its name, config schema, I/O types, and required metadata via <code>StepDef</code>. This powers validation, the step catalog, Studio, and the API.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">04</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Steps don't know where they live</h4>
            <p>A step works with domain types, not infrastructure. Ports define contracts. Adapters are swappable. Testing is trivial.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">05</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Fail comprehensively, not fast</h4>
            <p>The validator walks the full pipeline and collects every issue into a serializable list. You see all the problems at once, not one at a time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">06</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Stdlib unless proven otherwise</h4>
            <p><code>slog</code>, not logrus. <code>net/http</code>, not fiber. Every dependency is evaluated against a strict rubric.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Ready to build?</h2>
      <p>Read the getting started guide, browse the step catalog, or jump straight into the code.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Docs</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="about-section">
        <img src="/images/mozzy1.webp" alt="Mozzy, the Mosaigo mascot" loading="lazy" />
        <div class="about-text">
          <h3>Why "Mosaigo"?</h3>
          <p>A mosaic is made of many small tiles, each simple on its own, that together form something meaningful. That's how we think about pipelines: composable pieces that create a bigger picture. The "go" is for Go, the language that makes it possible.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:12px;">Mosaigo is open source, built in the open, and designed for real-time systems where every frame matters.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="/getting-started/">Docs</a>
        <a href="/steps/">Step Catalog</a>
